  "body": " What you need   An electronic weighing machine or a balance scale    Water    A large container    Graduated cylinder, ml        Measure and record the mass of an empty graduated cylinder in grams.    Pour mL of water into the graduated cylinder.    Weigh the graduated cylinder with mL of water and record the total mass.    Subtract the mass of the empty cylinder to find the mass of mL of water. Record it in the table.    Use the mass and volume of the water to calculate density. Record the density in g\/cm in the table below.  Density of water     Carefully pour out some water until only mL remains in the graduated cylinder.    Repeat steps to for mL of water.    Pour out more water until only mL remains. Repeat steps to again.    Finally, pour out water until you have mL remaining. Repeat the same process and record your results.    Look at the values of density for the different volumes.     Are they almost the same?    What does that tell you about the density of water?       What is the density of water in g\/cm ?      Calculating the density of different volumes of water    Volume of water  mL  mL  mL  mL    Mass of empty graduated cylinder (g)        Mass of graduated cylinder + water (g)        Mass of water (g)        Density of water (g\/cm )         "
